      <br><br><br>
      
      <table BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" Align="center" cellpadding=30  leftmargin="30" marginwidth="30" width="70%"  border="5"> 
	<UL>
	<tr>
	  <td>
	    <LI><b>T-Coffee</b>
	      <OL>
		<LI>Start with the default</LI>
		<LI>Try to combine alternative methods described in the section <B><i>What Are The Methods Already Integrated in T-Coffee</b></i>
		<LI>It can be interesting to combine two alternative matrices like Blosum and Pam</LI>
		<LI>Cheat! and use the reference alignment as an extra library!</LI>	
		<LI>Consider that each sequence is named according to the structure it is homologous to. Split the sequences, align each group and align the profiles</LI>
		<LI>Cheat again! This time with the two profiles.</LI>
	      </OL>
	    </LI>
	  </td>
	  <tr>
	    <td>
	      <LI><b>M-Coffee</b>
		<OL>
		  <LI>Try to combine the most diverse methods</LI>
		  <LI>Try Combining the methods one or two at a time</LI>
		</OL>
	      </LI>
	    </td>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
	    <td>
	      <LI><b>Expresso</b></LI>
	      <OL>
		<LI>use the T-Coffee server to get the Expresso template list</LI>
		<LI>Try to combine sequence and structure methods</LI>
	      </OL>
	    </LI>
	    </td>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
	    <td>
	      <LI><b>R-Coffee</b></LI>
	      <OL>
		<LI>use the various special modes: -special_mode=rcoffee OR rmcoffee and compare them with the default</LI>
	      </OL>
	    </LI>
	    </td>
	  </tr>
      </table>
